data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. WELCOME HOME!  Welcome to the peaceful tree lined streets of golf cart friendly Harbor Oaks - located in the quaint city of SAFETY HARBOR!  GREAT SCHOOLS!  Within minutes of DOWNTOWN AND PHILIPPE PARK on Old Tampa Bay! NO FLOOD ZONE! NEW ROOF AND A/C in 2023! THE SPLIT BEDROOM PLAN is ideal for privacy, with 2 BEDROOMS on one side and the master wing on the other side, which boasts a large bonus room that is attached.  This can be used for an office or workout room.  Convenient inside utility room.  The kitchen and living room walls are NOT load bearing and can be removed to open up the space.  Please ask for a sample photo of homes in the neighborhood that have done this.  The cozy Family Room features a stone WOOD BURNING FIREPLACE with sliders leading out to your patio, the perfect place to enjoy your morning coffee or evening barbeque. The backyard offers plenty of room for all your outdoor enjoyment, whether playing cornhole or grilling and chilling.  You could wake up to a beautiful stone courtyard that can be your tranquil outdoor living space - the possibilities are ENDLESS! No rear neighbors so there is plenty of privacy, peace and tranquility.  Wake up to the birds singing in the trees that surround the home -it's like living in your own nature preserve! Located very close to Folly Farms Nature Preserve, which features a hiking trail loop, butterfly garden, playground and special events. The perfectly quaint SAFETY HARBOR HAS A SMALL-TOWN FEEL, yet conveniently located to Countryside Mall, Tampa and St Pete-Clearwater International Airports, Downtown Tampa, St. Petersburg, and more! Safety Harbor's Main Street, just over a mile away…a short golf cart ride to DOWNTOWN SAFETY HARBOR, which is filled with restaurants - casual to fine dining, shops, a beautiful waterfront boardwalk and marina, fishing pier, library, farmer’s market, world famous Safety Harbor Spa and year-round live music and festivals and don't forget 3rd Friday of every month, where Main St. is shut down for all of your festivities and entertainment!!  Very close to Bayshore Dr., where you can soak up picturesque Tampa Bay views. Enjoy the tranquility of Philippe Park with fishing and trails just 10 minutes away, or enjoy in the beauty of Clearwater Beach, a mere 25-minute drive.  Schedule your viewing today!
